==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sundog
<hw>Sun"dog`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Meteorol.)</fld>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A luminous spot occasionally seen a few degrees from
the sun, supposed to be formed by the intersection of two or more halos,
or in a manner similar to that of halos.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A fragmentary rainbow; a small rainbow near the
horizon; -- called also <altname>dog</altname> and
<altname>weathergaw</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sundown</ent>⟦br⟧
